  <T n="name">0xF63D7C20<!--Grim Reaper Gameplay--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_GrimReaperGameplay_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:438a68d96b2e8835</T>
      <T n="text">0x75FDAF34<!--Sims may battle it out in a game of life or death when they <b>Challenge Grim to a Game</b> when a Sim has died. In order to do this, the game must already be placed on the lot before death occurs. After a Sim has died, and Grim has shown up to do his business, select a living Sim in the Household, choose one of the supported games and challenge Grim!\n\n<i>Supported games include: Chess, Darts (Get Together), Don't Wake the Llama (Get Together), Foosball (Get Together), Basketball (City Living), Ping-Pong (Discover University), Hopscotch (For Rent), Horseshoes (Outdoor Retreat), Bowling (Bowling Night).</i>--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_GrimReaperGameplay_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:438a68d96b2e8836</T>
      <T n="text">0xC638A7F6<!--The Grim Reaper can be friendly, dependable, and...romantic? Sims can gain a deeper relationship with Grim by <b>Socializing</b>, <b>Flirting</b>, and even <b>WooHooing</b>! As Sims increase friendship with Grim, more socials become unlocked. Once a Sim has become <b>Good Friends</b> with Grim, they can even call Grim to hang out.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_GrimReaperGameplay_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:438a68d96b2e8837</T>
      <T n="text">0x304CFD1A<!--Sims can even <b>Try for Baby</b> with Grim, no matter the gender of the Sim! <b>Grimborn Sims</b>, the offspring of Grim, are born with a distinct <b>Scythe Birthmark</b> and will live a little longer than normal Sims. When Grimborn Sims have children, the <b>Grim's Descendant</b> trait is passed on to mark Grim's legacy.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
